ere</a>, a nifty plugin available for all major browsers. You can write your notes in a special formatting language called <a href=\"http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/\">Markdown</a>, and this plugin applies slick formatting with the press of a button. If you’re not familiar with it, Markdown makes it very easy to structure and format your document by easily creating headings, lists, tables, and more. For code blocks, Markdown Here lets you choose from 30+ syntax highlighting themes and even customize them with CSS. All you do is start the code block with three backticks and the name of the language, and end the block with three more backticks, as shown below. For html code, use “xml”:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px !important;\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8008/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/screenshot-2014-04-07-at-19.53.42-.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-12\" src=\"http://localhost:8008/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/screenshot-2014-04-07-at-19.53.42-.png\" alt=\"screenshot 2014-04-07 at 19.53.42\" width=\"518\" height=\"479\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px !important;\">A click on the Markdown Here button or a quick press of the customizable hotkey changes the above Markdown into this:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px !important;\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8008/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/screenshot-2014-04-07-at-19.37.50-.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-13\" src=\"http://localhost:8008/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/screenshot-2014-04-07-at-19.37.50-.png\" alt=\"screenshot 2014-04-07 at 19.37.50\" width=\"521\" height=\"479\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px !important;\">How cool is that?! The style of these snippets is Tomorrow Night Eighties, but you can see the other available themes and languages on this <a href=\"http://highlightjs.org/static/test.html\">demo page</a> for highlight.js. Being a plugin, Markdown Here can’t be used in Word or other applications, but it is usable in some other places on the web such as Wordpress, Outlook Web App and Google Groups (<a href=\"https://github.com/adam-p/markdown-here/wiki/Compatibility\">full list</a>). I needed an easy way to style the code I share through Evernote and Gmail, and I found Markdown Here to be a great solution. I’ve also used it for quick formatting of lists in email.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 1.2em 0px !important;\">Do you have any other solutions for code styling? Other creative uses of Markdown or Markdown Here?</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"height: 0; font-size: 0em; padding: 0; margin: 0;\" title=\"MDH:PHA+SSByZWFsbHkgYXBwcmVjaWF0ZSB0aGUgd2F5IGdvb2QgdGV4dCBlZGl0b3JzIHJlbmRlciBu\r\naWNlbHkgc3R5bGVkLCBzeW50YXggaGlnaGxpZ2h0ZWQgY29kZS4gTm90IG9ubHkgaXMgaXQgdmlz\r\ndWFsbHkgYXR0cmFjdGl2ZSwgaXQgaGVscHMgeW91IGVhc2lseSBwaWNrIG91dCBrZXl3b3JkcyBx\r\ndWlja2x5IHNwb3QgbWlzc2luZyBxdW90ZXMgb3IgYnJhY2tldHMuIFVuZm9ydHVuYXRlbHkgY29w\r\neWluZyBhbmQgcGFzdGluZyBjb2RlIHNvbWV3aGVyZSBlbHNlIGFsbW9zdCBuZXZlciBwcmVzZXJ2\r\nZXMgdGhlIGhpZ2hsaWdodGluZywgYW5kIGV2ZW4gaWYgaXQgZG9lcywgZm9ybWF0dGluZyBhZGp1\r\nc3RtZW50cyBhcmUgb2Z0ZW4gc3RpbGwgcmVxdWlyZWQuIEFuIGV4YW1wbGUgY2FzZSBpcyB3aGVu\r\nIHNoYXJpbmcgYSBjb2RlIHNuaXBwZXQgd2l0aCBhIGNvbGxlYWd1ZSBieSBlbWFpbCBvciBFdmVy\r\nbm90ZS4gV2hldGhlciBJIGNvcHkgdGhlIGZvcm1hdHRlZCB0ZXh0IGZyb20gU3VibGltZSBUZXh0\r\nIDIgb3IgZnJvbSBFY2xpcHNlIChQeURldiBwbHVnaW4pLCB3aGVuIEkgcGFzdGUgaXQgaW50byB0\r\naGUgR21haWwgd2ViIGludGVyZmFjZSB0byBzZW5kIHRvIGEgZnJpZW5kLCB0aGUgdGV4dCBpcyBh\r\nbGwgYmxhY2sgYW5kIHRoZSBmb250IGNoYW5nZXMgdG8gYSBub24tbW9ub3NwYWNlIG9uZSBpbiBD\r\naHJvbWUgYW5kIEZpcmVmb3ggKE1hYykuIFNhZmFyaSBwcmVzZXJ2ZXMgdGhlIG1vbm9zcGFjZSBm\r\nb250LCBhbmQgc29tZXRpbWVzIGdldHMgdGhlIGZvbnQgY29sb3IgcmlnaHQsIGJ1dCBpZiB5b3Ug\r\ndXNlIGEgZGFyayBiYWNrZ3JvdW5kIGluIHlvdXIgdGV4dCBlZGl0b3IgbGlrZSBJIGRvLCB0aGUg\r\nZm9udCBjb2xvcnMgZG9uJ3QgbG9vayB3ZWxsIGluIGFuIG1lc3NhZ2Ugd2l0aCBhIHdoaXRlIGJh\r\nY2tncm91bmQgYW55d2F5LiBTbyBob3cgZG8geW91IHNoYXJlIGJlYXV0aWZ1bGx5IGZvcm1hdHRl\r\nZCBjb2RlIHdpdGggb3RoZXJzPyBbTWFya2Rvd24gSGVyZ